A defintion from www.informatica.com

Datawarehouse: A technology that aggregates data from one or more sources 
so that it can be compared and analyzed for great business intelligence.


a) Long running batch jobs
b) Optimized for read operations
c) Holds data from multiple sources
d) Holds data over a long period of time
e) Data may be lagged, not real time

Ex of DWH tools:
Vertica
Teradata
Oracle
IBM

Apache Hive is an opensource Datawarehouse tool
Hive is part of the larger Hadoop ecosystem

Hive runs on top of the Hadoop distributed computing framework.
Hive stores its data in HDFS
